modName: RaceMenu female Half Aeterna (High Elf) preset for Enderal
summary: Pretty average female Half Aeterna/High Elf RaceMenu preset for Enderal in pink colors.
descriptionHtml:
[size=4]Description:[/size]
Pretty average female Half Aeterna/High Elf RaceMenu preset for Enderal. Default Enderal face looked like my character was already turning into Blue Death and any preset from nexus I tried didn't work properly, probably Enderal fault (or my hands grow out of a wrong place). So I downloaded RaceMenu, pulled some sliders, cleaned it up in face sculpt a bit and got this, not half bad, but could be better. If you don't like any color, it's easy to change in RaceMenu. You can do pretty much anything with it since it's HALF Aeterna. Who knows how they turn out? [color=#ffe599]Let me know if it doesn't look like on the screenshots (only if you are using Enderal of course).[/color]Also let me know if you know of any texture that is less smooth than the one I use, but is still very smooth.

[size=4]Requirements:[/size]
This preset only requires Enderal's Skyrim.esm, this hairstyle comes packaged in it. So nothing required except RaceMenu and Enderal.

[size=4]Installation:[/size]
Place "preset.jslot" in "...Skyrim\Data\SKSE\Plugins\CharGen\Presets\"

[size=4]Mod list[/size]
In case you want to [color=#d5a6bd]get similar looks[/color] or [color=#cccccc]get some mod suggestions[/color] for Enderal. It's pretty dirty, but "it just works", because I'm using Mod Organizer. Use it too, it's better than NMM. Just make sure you install it in the same order with overwrite if you don't use MO:

[list]
[*][color=#cccccc]AlwaysPickUpBooksV41 — pick up books when you don't want to read them or read them when you don't want to steal.[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]RaceMenu[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]Backup Movement Speed Reduction — slower backpedaling, nerfs ranged PCs from godlike level to demigod.[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]Enhanced Soultrap — just better soultrap.[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]Realistic AI Detection - Low Interior Low Exterior — doesn't really do much in Enderal since most mobs are semi-hostile.[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]ShowRaceMenu PreCacheKiller — stability.[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]Warmer Magic Lights v2 Compatibility Patches — makes it so that magic light does not burn your eyes out with Enderal lighting tweaks.[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]Smart Cast — you can cast some spells without switching to them, like magic light, summon ancestor, etc.[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]Realistic Force[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]ShowRaceMenu Alternative - Latest Version — in case you like this preset so much that you want to change race to high elf first, without breaking your game.[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]Dimonized UNP BASE Skinny body V1dot2[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]No More Glowing Edges Mod[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]Smaller Cursor[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]Unread Books Glow[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]Dimonized 1dot51body textures[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]Dimonized DIMface2[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]Increased character height — helps you actually see something when you're walking through grass in Enderal.[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]Difficult Archery — accuracy reduction for NPC archers.[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]Better Hand Mesh for UNP UNPB UNPC[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]Feminine Hands CBBE UNP[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]High Poly Feet and Hands for UNP Body — there's a link to this mod at [url=http://www.tesgeneral.com/waifu]www.tesgeneral.com/waifu[/url], it also has good tips on making your own looks.[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]Fair Skin Complexion — put other skin texture mod here if you don't like this one.[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]Fair Skin Complexion Blank Detail Map[/color]
[*][color=#cccccc]Better Jumping — for jumping during sprint mostly.[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]Natural Eyes — contains FemaleEyesHumanDemon that you can switch to if this elf [/color][color=#ff00ff]wasn't pink enough for you[/color][color=#d5a6bd].[/color]
[*][color=#d5a6bd]Natural Eyes alternative — use this for yellow eyes on the screenshot that look better than vanilla, but it's not required.[/color]
[/list]
